                            The frequency of hood cleaning depends on your cooking volume and type of cuisine. Most restaurants require cleaning every 1-3 months. High-volume establishments, especially those using a lot of grease (like barbecue or fried food restaurants), may need monthly cleaning. We recommend following NFPA guidelines, which suggest cleaning frequency based on your specific cooking operations. We can assess your kitchen and provide a customized cleaning schedule recommendation during your first service.
